## 2. Acceptance criteria

The Next.js app ships when:

- [ ] `pnpm dev` boots without warnings; the app loads at `/`
- [ ] `pnpm build` produces a clean production bundle
- [ ] Every route has at least a smoke-test (HTTP 200 for happy path)
- [ ] All Server Components that read user data go through the auth
      middleware (no orphaned `db.query` in unauthed routes)
- [ ] Tailwind classes follow the design-system tokens (no inline `style=`)
- [ ] Drizzle migrations run cleanly against the cloud Postgres
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm lint` are both green

## 3. Non-goals

- No SSR-only rendering — embrace App Router + Server Components
- No client-side data fetching for content the server can render
- No custom auth — Clerk owns authentication
- No raw SQL — use Drizzle for every query (pgvector ops can use
  `sql\`...\`` template tags but stay schema-validated)

